#X text 291 465 A cosine waveshaper is not rectification but is symmetric on the horizontal axis and also destroys the polarity symmetry \, similarly to rectification and effectively sounding an octave higher for the same reason. Hence \, we must halv the frequency in these cases., f 42;
#X obj 665 243 max~ 0;
#X obj 599 243 min~ 0;
#X text 31 32 A half wave rectification can be implemented by simply ignoring negative values with [max~ 0] (or [min~ 0] to only preserve the negative part). We can also use [hip~] to remove the DC offset so the wave is not only constrained to the positive phase. A full wave rectification turns the negative into positive and can be implemented with [abs~]., f 79;
